answers.body_markdown:
I&#39;d suggest to use TestContainers to emulate postgres. TestContainers will run postgres database in docker container during tests. Test will connect to this docker database and run its code.

NOTE: Docker is needed to run TestContainers.

`application.yml` will looks like:
```yaml
spring:
  flyway:
    locations: classpath:db/migration
  datasource:
    driver-class-name: org.postgresql.Driver
    username: postgres
    password:
    url: jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/test
```
You can change flyway to another migration tool that you like.

`application-test.yml` will look like:
```yaml
spring:
  datasource:
    driver-class-name: org.testcontainers.jdbc.ContainerDatabaseDriver
    url: jdbc:tc:postgresql:11.1///test
  jpa:
    database-platform: org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQL9Dialect
    hibernate:
      ddl-auto: validate
```
`pom.xml` should contain following dependencies:
```xml
    &lt;properties&gt;
        &lt;org.testcontainers.version&gt;1.12.5&lt;/org.testcontainers.version&gt;
    &lt;/properties&gt;
    &lt;dependencies&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.postgresql&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;postgresql&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.testcontainers&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;testcontainers&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;${org.testcontainers.version}&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.testcontainers&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;postgresql&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;${org.testcontainers.version}&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        ...
    &lt;/dependencies&gt;
```
Test should look like:
```java
@DataJpaTest
@AutoConfigureTestDatabase(replace = AutoConfigureTestDatabase.Replace.NONE)
class TestcontainerApplicationTests {
    @Autowired
    UserRepository userRepository;

    @Test
    void contextLoads() {
        User user = new User();
        user.setName(&quot;test&quot;);
        userRepository.save(user);
    }
}
```
This code snipplet will add TestContainer. It will run PostgreSQL database in docker. 

Here is [sample code][1].


  [1]: https://github.com/evgenycheryomushkin/testcontainer

