It is possible to exclude a directory from inspection with SpotBugs, though the approach is different to the one you described for PMD. It is a two step process:

1. First [create an XML filter file][1] specifying the criteria for the directory(s) to be excluded.

2. Then, in **pom.xml** refer to that that file using the optional `&lt;excludeFilterFile&gt;` setting. Unfortunately, [the documentation for that setting][2] is very brief.

As a simple example:

1. Create a filter file named **ignore.xml** containing the following which refers to a directory named **mydir**:

        &lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;
        &lt;FindBugsFilter&gt;
            &lt;Match&gt;
                &lt;Source name=&quot;~mydir\..*&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/Match&gt;
        &lt;/FindBugsFilter&gt;

    The documentation for [the `&lt;Source&gt;` tag is here][3]. See the section on [Java element name matching][4] for details on how to specify the **name** of the `&lt;Source&gt;`.

2. Then in **pom.xml**, in the specification for **spotbugs-maven-plugin**, include an `&lt;excludeFilterFile&gt;` tag so that **mydir** is ignored by SpotBugs:

        &lt;configuration&gt;
          &lt;excludeFilterFile&gt;ignore.xml&lt;/excludeFilterFile&gt;
        &lt;/configuration&gt;

Notes:

- There is also an `&lt;includeFilterFile&gt;` tag. See the section titled **Specifying which bug filters to run** in [the usage documentation][5].

- As well as `Source`, SpotBugs provides several other ways to specify what code is to be included or excluded from checking. See the filter file documentation for the `Package`, `Class`, `Method`, `Local`, `Field` and `Type` tags.

- Place your `&lt;excludeFilterFile&gt;` in the root of your project.


  [1]: https://spotbugs.readthedocs.io/en/stable/filter.html
  [2]: https://spotbugs.github.io/spotbugs-maven-plugin/check-mojo.html#excludeFilterFile
  [3]: https://spotbugs.readthedocs.io/en/stable/filter.html#source
  [4]: https://spotbugs.readthedocs.io/en/stable/filter.html#java-element-name-matching
  [5]: https://spotbugs.github.io/spotbugs-maven-plugin/usage.html

